Grossly overpriced goods, timed 2hr wifi, pretty venue but there are FAR better cafes in the neighborhood. Truly.  Pros: Clean venue, tranquil hiphop forward playlist (madlib, jaydilla, 9th wonder), good day light bleeds in, friendly and attentive staff.  Cons: Bagel with butter - $3.75, drip coffee - $2.75 watery with a lovely film of coffee grinds AND THE CLINCHER - wifi is “complimentary” for 2 hours with each sale transaction. I use coffee shops OFTEN. This 2hr wifi limit with purchase rationing has not happened to me since visiting an east African dictatorship country where internet usage is heavily monitored. Superior, more reasonably priced bagels can be found 2 blocks away (e.g. Bagel Pub). Superior, more chill cafes with better coffee, truly complimentary wifi and background tunes just blocks away.  USUALLY cafe spots like repeat customers and encourage a sense of community. I cannot imagine Manhattanville sharing those values. I couldn’t bring myself to award it more than 2 stars.

This homey little cafe is a bit of a unicorn — plenty of seating, lots of accessible outlets, free and reliable wifi, and great coffee and food to sustain you during your stay. As a result, plenty of creatives and students gather here. During decent weather, the large windows open up, which makes it a pleasant spring and summer spot. There's also a restroom (a bit of an NYC anomaly) that's well-kept, so you can settle in for the long haul if you need a day of solid work. One note, though, is that the music can be a bit loud at times, so be sure to bring headphones if you'd rather pick your own quiet playlist.
